animal.description:
This pretty lady is Mama Baker! She is a ~3 year old mixed breed who weighs about 60 pounds.  When she first came to us, she had a belly full of puppies.  They all found their forever homes and Mama Baker is still eager to find her pawfect match!

Mama Baker is sweet as pie, but she is also very timid at first. She'll need an adopter who will go slow and be patient with her while she adjusts to her new surroundings - new situations can be scary for a timid gal like her. An experienced dog owner who is willing to work with her on her fear would be ideal.  Once she warms up and realizes she's safe and loved, she will love you unconditionally.  Mama Baker is very gentle and loves to snuggle and lay her head on her person's lap. Keep in mind that her unconditional love can also lead her to be protective of her people.  For this reason, she needs a home with no other dogs.  It will also be necessary for her new family to let her hangout in another room if there are visitors. 

Mama Baker prefers to hangout with adults and warms up to them much quicker than children, so she kindly requests no kids under the age of 16 in her forever family.  As with any visitor, if you have children that visit or neighborhood kids, Mama Baker would feel much safer and more comfortable if you let her hang out in another room.  A secure fence is a requirement to adopt Mama Baker.

If you can provide Mama Baker with the home environment she's looking for, apply to adopt today!  Her minimum adoption fee is $235 plus a $12 fee, if 4 months or older, for rabies registration for McLean County residents.

She has been spayed, microchipped, vaccinated, heartworm checked, dewormed, and is on flea and heartworm preventatives.

For information about this dog's breed(s), visit: http://www.dogbreedinfo.com/abc.htm 

To fill out our adoption application, go to: http://fs16.formsite.com/WishBoneCanineRescue/adoptionapplication/index.html

animal.description: Meet Jayden! Jayden is a dashingly handsome 1-year-old mixed-breed guy who currently weighs about 51 pounds. He came to SFAS as a stray found wandering the city. Now he is ready for a loving family to call his own. Here at the shelter Jayden has been friendly with humans and dogs alike and enjoys going on nice long walks with his favorite person. If you have other dogs at home please let the scheduler know you would like to bring them along for a Meet n' Greet. Jayden's adoption fee is $130. He is neutered, microchipped and has age-appropriate vaccinations. A licensing/microchip fee may apply. Interested in meeting with Jayden or being added to his waitlist? Please call (505) 983-4309 x 1610 and leave a voicemail message that includes the DOG'S NAME, plus YOUR NAME and A PHONE NUMBER - OR e-mail this information to adoption@sfhumanesociety.org. A scheduler will call you back within 48 hours to confirm your request. SFAS offers a variety of excellent training classes, seminars and Trainer Talks led by animal behavior professionals. These are $50 off for animals adopted from any shelter or rescue group! Due to current COVID-19 restrictions, classes and talks are all presented virtually using Zoom. For course descriptions, schedules and registration, visit https://sfhumanesociety.org/our-programs/behavior-training/group-training-classes/ for classes and https://sfhumanesociety.org/our-programs/behavior-training/special-seminars-and-workshops/ for seminars and Trainer Talks.

animal.description: Ladybug was turned into the shelter by a good samaritan who took care of her and her pups when she showed up at his house two months ago. She has been living outside in a kennel and gets along with other dogs. She is about 47 lbs and is very excited and friendly and needs a little direction. She does not like CATS. She likes to play with a ball and will play fetch - she also likes rope toys. She is treat motivated and working on basic commands such as sit, stay, down, and leave it. She does pull a little bit here and here when walking. On a short lead she is content beside you. She will tuck her tail and cowers a bit at loud noises. She likes to be close to you and cuddle. Ladybug got to go Home for the Holidays. While she was away for the week we found that she: loves people and other dogs but needs to be slowly introduced and integrated into the 4 legged part of the family. She loves stuffed and squeaky toys. She is working on becoming housebroken and will walk around when she has to go out. Ladybug will sleep on the floor on a doggy bed if you want her to but prefers to sleep in the people bed. Please call and schedule an appointment if you would like to meet her.

animal.description:
This beautiful girl is Magnolia and she is looking for her forever home. Magnolia came to Animal Friends via transfer with another shelter. She is about 3 years old and 75 pounds.
Magnolia is deaf. She would need a family that would be willing to work with her and learn how to communicate effectively with her. Magnolia also has lots of energy. She enjoys going for walks, sniffing, and exploring. Using her brain is another one of Magnolia's favorite pass times. She would love a new family that would be willing to keep her active and continue her training. 
Magnolia would do best in an adult only home. She can be a little selective with other dogs and she can not live with cats. A family with dog experience would be beneficial for Magnolia as well.
If you are interested in adopting Magnolia, you will schedule several meet and greet appointments to work one on one with the staff and volunteers who know her best. This will give you time to get to know Magnolia and her cues, while starting to bond with her.
The first step to any adoption is filling out an application (thinkingoutsidethecage.org/application). If you have any questions, please reach out to the adoption team (adoptioninfo@thinkingoutsidethecage.org)

animal.description:
MEET RENO!!

Underdog Rescue does not physically have this dog in its possession. He is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A4511568.

Reno is a beautiful brindle dog that needs a furever home! Reno loves to go for a walk and can't wait to get out of his kennel so he can GO!! He will start out in a run because he's so happy to get out but once he walks for a while, he settles down and walks at a fast pace. He likes to go out to the play yard and do the "zoomies" and he'll also come up and "sit" for a treat. Reno has shown that he doesn't like the other dogs in the kennels next to him and he will definitely need a dog introduction for someone who already has dogs at home.

If you think you'd like to meet Reno and see if he's a good fit in your home, come to the MCACC shelter today. Reno would love to go home soon!

If you are interested in saving this pet, please reach out via this link: https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/foster/BPAZ/Dog

To actually visit with this pup, please make an appointment here: https://mcaccappointments.as.me/adopt. NOTE: People who sign up for these appointments often no-show, and we have seen that you can generally show up and let them know you are there to meet this particular dog and the shelter will squeeze you in, except from 12-3PM or closer to the 6PM closing time. (Please know this is not a guarantee). If the dog is at risk, please ask for a supervisor to meet that particular dog.

*Please Note: This animal is courtesy posted for the Maricopa County Shelter; UNDERDOG RESCUE DOES NOT HAVE THIS DOG. MCACC is located at 2500 S. 27th Avenue, Phoenix. Different adoption fees/policy may apply. Please visit MCACC's website http://www.maricopa.gov/pets/locations.aspx for hours. You may also wish to call 602-506-7387 (PETS) and provide the animal's A# above to verify is still available.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Online Adoption Application 

Jesper is a a handsome young boy. He's as tall as a med sized dog, but a thin frame. He loves to sit on your lap and being cradled like a baby.
Unfortunately, we believe Jesper may have been mistreated and is affraid of being hurt. He's looking for a very patient family that uses care when handling him. He can be sensitive to touch during certain situations and may be a little nippy to let you know he's uncomfortable and doesn't like something. We recommend adults only in the home.

Jesper may be better as an only pet or maybe one other pet. His housebreaking is still in progress. He does better with a consistent schedule and may need to be crated when unsupervised or use a gate to limit his access.

animal.description:
Dexter is a good boy.

And, staff here is already falling in love with him.

Dexter is friendly, playful and very affectionate.

We are told that he also gets along with most other dogs too.

This guy is very smart and already knows some basic commands. He is able to escape 4 foot fences so he needs a sturdy solid fence in his yard.

You can tell that he is eager to learn more so we hope potential adopters will want to continue his obedience education. He’d make a great companion for your adventures or perhaps even agility, nose-work and more!

Dexter was abandoned in a malnourished state, but thankfully he hasn’t let his past life put a damper on his sunny disposition.

If you have an active home and are ready to give this good boy a forever home please fill out an application today.

animal.description: Viktor is a two-year-old, 53-pound Pit Bull and Labrador mix.  He was turned in at the county shelter in early November as a stray.  He wasn’t finding his family while at county, so he has come to Home Fur Good to see if he can find that perfect fit.  When Viktor first arrived at county, he was so nervous around the leash that they had to use the transport bucket to wheel him from place to place.  By the end of his stay at county they were able to take him on walks off-campus.  HFG looks forward to having Viktor join the Dog Walking Club to help him gain his confidence on leash adventures.  Viktor is very friendly and willingly comes out of his kennel for anyone; he is always amped up for an adventure. The adoption fee is $225 and includes spaying/neutering, age-appropriate vaccinations, microchipping, and a free wellness visit at Phoenix Mountain Animal Hospital. Our adoption hours are Thursday-Saturday from 11:00 am-4:00 pm by appointment only.

animal.description:
Meet Charlie! Charlie is a 2 year old male blue brindle pit/shepherd mix who was released to the shelter because of his bad manners. Charlie got to where he was nipping at the owner and will need time and training to teach this handsome guy some manners. He has been great with the shelter staff but does not seem fond of other dogs. We also do not believe he likes cats but he does seem to be house broken since he keeps his kennel pretty clean. We would not recommend he go to a home with kids since he has a tendency to nip. Charlie weighs around 58 pounds and is HEARTWORM NEGATIVE as of 1-12-21.

animal.description:
***The first step in adopting is to submit an application at www.emmetcountyanimalshelter.org we are struggling with volunteers being out so your patience is very much appreciated!***

Chance is the name of this fluffy fella. In 2018 Chance was in a high kill facility and needed our help. Chance arrived to us covered in ticks and getting sick. Once we had his nursed back to health he showed us how happy and goofy he is. A few months later Chance was adopted. In early 2020 he had become protective of his new human and had an issue with her boyfriend. For safety Chance was returned to us. Chance lives in a foster home with a male and female and does not show these behaviors to them. Chance has been adopted briefly to another home where he would growl and lunge at the man of the house but never the woman or son. We have introduced him to many men at stores and in home and have yet to have an issue with him ourselves. We are looking for a specific type of home for Chance to help him succeed in finding his forever home.

For Chance we are looking for a home that will have no kids, no cats, no dogs under 40lbs, no other small animals. All of that is due to his prey drive and history. Chance will also need a home that is able

to walk him or use tie outs

to let him out. He will run away off lead and can escape a secure privacy fence by climbing over it.

The most important thing we will be looking for is someone with experience working with dogs or the ability to work

closely with a trainer to overcome any issues that come up.

Chance is a happy, bouncy, sweet boy.

He is 4-5 years old and about 40lbs.

He loves hard and wants to show his affection to anyone he trusts. Chance loves other dogs once he gets to know them but does not like to be rushed by them at first or he will become defensive. He has 7 other dogs in his foster home and he gets along with everyone great. He is kennel trained, house trained, and has leash manners once he gets in the groove. We hope to find Chance the perfect home to work with him if things get tough and love him endlessly as he will them.

He has a history of being a runner but is comfortable on leash and on a tie out. He can escape a secure fence. He is house and kennel trained. Chance is a happy guy looking for a lifelong companion to help him be the fantastic guy he can be! If your family could use a wonderful fur friend like Chance please go to our website at www.emmetcountyanimalshelter.org to fill out the dog adoption application. Chance is ready for his forever home and his foster family is ready to rescue another pup in need. His adoption fee is $225.00_ and he is fully vetted and Microchipped.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Meet Chief! This handsome boy is a laid-back gentle giant. Born around January 2018, he is thin at 70 pounds. His ideal weight is closer to 90 pounds, and he'll get there after enjoying lots of yummy vittles and soaking up more tender loving care.

Sweet Chief is very loving. He loves being petted and being near his humans. He doesn't need toys to feel happy; he is super content just finding a comfy spot to lay inside or outside. At night, he loves sleeping next to you on the floor even when he has access to the rest of the house. He's hasn't yet shown interest in getting on furniture.

Chief does really well with someone home with him all the time. He also does fine when his people leave the house, he just needs a few minutes to get used to the idea, then he relaxes until you return.

He loves exploring and going on adventures! He is the best wingman on hiking trips - everyone along the way loves him and he is so good on the leash.

Chief must have a large fenced-in yard with lots of space to roam, run, and relax. Outdoors is his happy place!

Mr. Man (one of his nicknames) is house trained and he rarely barks. He has no need to be crated, and that's good, because he hates it!

He really enjoys car rides, but he needs convincing to get in it. For now, he needs a booty assist. In time, he might associate car rides with fun adventures, then he might climb in willingly. He wants to join you in a front seat! You'll need a firm blocking technique or strong netting to keep him safely in the back.

He adores being outside. He needs a sturdy, tall fence to keep him contained in the yard.

He is nice with other dogs, and he does fine with them at mealtime.

Chief will be an ideal family dog. He yearns for people to include him in their daily lives.

SPIN Pyrs are all in foster homes in the Dallas/Fort Worth area. Potential adopters are asked to make travel arrangements if they live elsewhere. All SPIN dogs are spayed or neutered, current on vaccinations and on heartworm prevention. Please go to our website www.SpinRescue.org and fill out an application for this great Great Pyrenees!

- PLEASE NOTE THAT ONLY APPROVED ADOPTERS WILL BE PERMITTED TO MEET OUR RESCUES - WE ARE A FOSTER BASED RESCUE AND ALL OF OUR DOGS LIVE WITH US AS FAMILY. 

Thanks for considering a rescue pup!

animal.description: Hi! My name is Scout, and Im one of the newbies from Wilco. I love when my friends stop by my kennel to say hi. I do a little tap dance when they do ... (especially if theres a treat or two involved). Im starting to figure out my new digs, and while I miss my friends at Wilco, Im making so many more here at AAC! Im also starting some force/fear free training with my new human friends, and am so excited to know so many good boy tricks! I love ALL THE THINGS!!!- Cheese, chicken, hot dogs, lamb loaf, training treats, bones ... Oh! And dont mind my big-boy borks when you first walk up... its just my way of saying Hi! I am silly and goofy and full of playful energy, the kind of dog that will have you laughing at my antics every day. The kind of dog that has a special knack for bringing a smile to your face, no matter what kind of day you're having! Im dreaming of a forever home with my own person. Is that you? Scout is one of our very first Shelter Exchange Program participants from Williamson County Regional Animal Shelter. The Shelter Exchange Program is an innovative new partnership to give longstay dogs stuck in the shelter system exposure to new adopters and a new community in hopes of finding them the perfect family. Three of our longstay dogs are now at Williamson County Regional Animal Shelter while three of theirs are now with us. Click here to view my behavior notes.

animal.description:
Baby is a very sweet and loving dog who loves to play in the snow. She is playful and bonds closely with the people she knows and loves.

Baby would do best with an owner that has dog experience that can work with her and train her. She is eager to learn and is a quick learner. She is highly treat motivated and would do well with a positive reinforcement based training regimen. We have been working on the "touch" command with her to help with her focus, and she also knows "sit".

She would do best with owners who have an active lifestyle, and that can give her lots of enrichment and exercise. Baby is not able to go home to a family with other animals as she is reactive due to past trauma. 

We think it is best that Baby not go home to a home with children under the age of 15 due to her energy level and fear based behaviors towards children due to previous experiences. 

Baby is an amazing girl who just needs someone to take a chance on her so she can be the most precious version of herself.

If you are interested in temporarily fostering her, please send us an email adopt@foxvalleypets.org .

animal.description:
Lovely Lucy is big (some might call her big-boned), beautiful lady who is learning to blossom. Timid and sensitive in new environments, Lucy was at first reserved and unsure about kennel life but she's slowly started to realize that people can be friends! And as she does, she shows off her more fun and bubbly personality. In the hubbub of the kennel, Lucy's adorably wrinkled face is often creased into a look of concern and she is quite watchful of all that's going on - but in quieter, peaceful moments she reveals her capacity for affectionate and love! Plus, you will discover a delightful secret soon after getting to know her... Lucy has a charmingly derpy overbite! Lucy would likely thrive in a quiet home where she can build her confident and trust - we believe once she settles, she will make an adoring companion. Lucy is estimated to be around 4 years old and she weighs a slightly thick 78 lbs. 

Visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog to set up a meet with Luc
Due to COVID-19, CITY DOGS is currently doing adoptions by APPOINTMENT ONLY. Please visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog to request a meet and greet! 

Questions? Email: citydogs@city.cleveland.oh.us | Call: (216) 664-3476
Visit: 9203 Detroit Avenue Cleveland, OH 44102

Hours:
10 AM - 3 PM Monday, Wednesday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday
10 AM - 6 pm Tuesday & Thursday

Fee: $61 | Includes spay/neuter, shots, microchip, license, 30 days free pet insurance (when registered upon adoption)

The CITY DOGS mission is to increase adoptions from the City Kennel by changing the image of the pit bulls who make up the majority of the kennel population, by preparing all adoptable dogs in the kennel for lives in loving homes and by creating as many opportunities as possible for the public to meet and get to know our dogs for the terrific pets they are meant to be.

Our Adoption Process...
Here's a little about how things work:
All of the CITY DOGS posted for adoption are available for direct adoption from the kennel, unless noted otherwise. You must schedule a meet with a dog in advance - we are not currently accepting walk-ins. Please look online first to see if there are any dogs you think would be a good fit for your home before scheduling a meet. To get the process started, visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog and fill out the form. One of our adoption counselors will get in touch to schedule and confirm your meet! At the kennel, an adoption counselor will introduce you and your family to the adoptable dogs, share information we know about them, and discuss our suggested ways for successfully integrating a new dog into your home. You are welcome to meet multiple dogs. If the dog you adopt is already fixed, he or she may leave with you that day - otherwise, the dog can go home after receiving the spay or neuter surgery.)

About Our Dogs: All available dogs have gone through a behavioral and medical assessment. This assessment is a snapshot of who the dog is at that given time. We cannot make any guarantees with regard to behavior, temperament or health of any City Dog once they are in the home. Most of our dogs are picked up as strays, so we do not know what kind of home environment they were living in (i.e. with kids, other dogs or other cats), nor do we know if most of them are house trained. Everything we know about them is based on volunteer and staff observations. We do have some dogs in foster homes, where they will have more information about how the dog is in a home environment. It is very hard to tell with certainty whether or not a dog will be good with kids, cats or another dog. If you have kids in the home or another dog, we do require that they be present for a meet and greet with the dog you are considering for adoption.

Heath/Vaccinations: Dogs that are adopted directly from the kennel need to go to your personal vet within two weeks of leaving the kennel. All dogs receive their DAPPL, Rabies, and Bordatella vaccines, though you may be required to get follow up boosters. All dogs come microchipped and with a Cuyahoga County license.?

animal.description:
Hi there, my name is Kenzie and I'm a 2 year old Pit Mix. I'm very shy when I first meet people. The shelter has me very overwhelmed. I'm finally starting to come around, but it's going to take some time. When I first arrived I was so scared that I slipped out of my original collar and ran right back into the back seat of my owner's car. I was brought to Lakeshore PAWS because my family was moving and couldn't take me with. I am house trained and crate trained. I'm really one of the sweetest girls. I'd prefer that my new home is calmer and has kids 10+ in it that are friendly and respectful. I want my new family to know that I will take time to adjust. I also am skittish, so they need to use caution while I adjust to my surroundings. I know a few tricks like sit, shake, down, and come. I enjoy sleeping in bed with you and cuddling at night. I haven't been around cats before, but my previous family said that I interacted just fine with other dogs. I'm quiet in my kennel for the most part. I sit on my bed and watch the world go on around me. My heart is broken, but I know another family can help me pick up the pieces and mend it back together. Once I warm up I'm a playful girl that enjoys treats and stuffed toys. I hope you give me the chance I've been waiting for to be with a family forever.

Love, Kenzie

Love, Venus

animal.description:
Hi every one, my name is Lilly Mae and I'm a 7.5 year old Hound Mix. I am looking for a fun home where I can play and get all of the attention to myself. I'd like to be the only pet in the home getting all of the treats and toys a girl could ever want. You'll be happy to know that I'm house trained and crate trained. You don't have to worry about me making a mess. Loud noises such as fireworks scare me. I've been tossing around some stuffed toys here at the adoption center and some of the volunteers have been running around with me outside. I am a chunky girl weighing in at 71 pounds. I need to lose some weight but it's hard because I just love food so much! I'd prefer that any kids in the home are 12+ because I am not a fan of a lot of chaos and I enjoy my space. My new family should be familiar with Hounds! We like to bark, play outside, and we enjoy our good. I seem to prefer being around men rather than women, but I interact just fine with females. I'm a social girl and I like to greet every one in the room. I sit nicely when asked. A senior girl like myself shouldn't be in a shelter. I should be in a home curled up on the couch, or maybe a dog bed by the fireplace. I can snooze while you'll cook or clean. I promise to be a good girl. I just need a family to promise to love me unconditionally and spoil me for the rest of my life!

Love, Lilly Mae

animal.description:
Bernard – German Shepherd mix – 2yrs. – male (62 lbs.)

Introducing our special boy, Bernard. Bernard was picked up on a reservation where he had been an outside dog running with a number of other dogs; he had no real home. When he got to the county shelter he was considered almost feral, he had rarely been touched by humans. They worked with Bernard for weeks and he came around much faster than expected. We decided to bring him in with us to help continue his progress in a much more “hands-on” environment. We’re smaller and are able to give more individualized attention. Bernard is doing really well with us. He is learning to trust people and loves those that he’s comfortable with! We’ve found that if you take him for a long walk, he thinks you’re his best friend. Bernard is very sweet, loving, and curious of all that life has to offer. He’s looking for a calm home with understanding owners that will take their time to introduce him to new things. He’d do best with another dog in the home, as it helps with his confidence. We know that, with love and patience, Bernard will grow into an amazing companion and his family will have his unconditional love and devotion. To have the opportunity to meet our sweet boy, please fill out an application today. 

https://form.jotform.com/91891552799173

animal.description:
Hi best friends, my name is Quinn and I’m a beautiful 3 year old Pit Mix. I was found curled up on the porch of a house that I didn’t belong to. A nice lady brought me to Lakeshore PAWS and I’ve been living a good life ever since. Now it’s time for me to live my best life. You should know some important information about me. While I’m not the biggest fan of other dogs, I was in a holiday foster home with kids and I was a good girl overall. I am well behaved in my crate at night if my family feels I need to be in one, but my foster mom thinks I’d be okay without one. I get a little nippy and mouthy when I get bored and want to play, but I easily transition to a toy if given one. I am a little difficult to walk as I pull a lot and need some redirection. Treats and training will hopefully help with this. I’m very sweet and I just love people. I was good and not over reactive to people coming over. I slept by my foster family’s feet when they watched tv. I only got on the couch once, but otherwise I never got on the furniture even if I was invited. I’m a little nutty in the car, but with more exposure and training I just know I will be the perfect girl. I can’t wait to meet you!

Love, Quinn

animal.description: We have the most delightful bonded older gentlemen available to brighten up the home where they can find the love they lost.  Rex and Renny are two charming guys who have become orphans in their mature years.  Rex is a smiling Boxer mix who will turn 9 in March.  Renny is a lovable Golden Retriever mix who will turn 9 in June.  Both boys grew up together from puppyhood with a kind-hearted gentleman who loved them dearly. Sadly their owner died in November from Covid, leaving them to carry on by themselves.  The boys had the best care which included a senior support group so they are in very good health.  They have some arthritis to deal with but it does not stop them from enjoying a little wrestling now and then.  They are just a lot of fun.  Rex and Renny are two wonderful companions that are low maintenance.  They still enjoy doggie daycare once a week.  Rex and Renny are sweet old souls with so much more to give .....  each one is special in his own way.  They are happy to lounge around the house or soak up sun in the backyard. They don't require lots of walks.  Their hearts are longing to fill another home with the brightness and joy that has become part of them.  Contact us on how to meet Rex and Renny and give your heart away.

animal.description:
Lolli is our "miracle girl" as she was hit by a car and had major surgery, as her organs were pushed up into her lungs.  She has recovered very nicely, though she does still have a limp/

Lolli loves to play with other dogs, and would not do well without one in the home.

She does tend tp have separation anxiety, so the best match for Lolli would be a retired couple, or someone who works from home, so she is not left alone to much.

Lolli does not do well crated...she tries to escape and gets very worked up, if confined.

She is fully vetted and a great girl, but not a lap dog, as she like to run and play and let you pet her when she wants it...not picked up and put in your lap.

animal.description:
KEANU is a helping dog. He's playful with dogs, excellent with cats, and affectionate with humans. He's been helping a dog named Haley who was thrown from a building - he motivated her through her healing and is her best friend. He also became instant friends with a deaf dog named Daisy who's the same size and almost looks identical. He's welcoming to new puppies in the rescue as well. He has his own story to tell -- when he was a puppy, he was placed in a sealed box and left on the side of the road. He is a bit shy at first, especially with men, but his true nature, once he feels secure, is very playful and affectionate. 

His adoption fee includes his neutering, vaccinations, microchip, and deworming. He was born on a reservation we work with in 2019.

We would love Keanu to adopt with Haley or Daisy if you don't already have a young playful female dog. 

We have specific ADOPTION and COVID rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy. 

First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application to see if the pet is still available. (Please do not call or text). We'll send you a link to the application.

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal. If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this. 

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you. 

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets. 

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets. At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we), keep to a properly distanced social distance and have hand sanitizer and your own leash.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. No young children for our adoptions please.

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos  etc will make our work worthwhile :-))

Our volunteers and adoption board are working diligently with an overload of inquiries since Covid to match families and forever pets. Our workload on the reservations has also increased. We're sorry, but if you email us with questions that are already answered here or fill out an application that does not fit the parameters of our procedures we will not be able to reply to you. Thank you for your understanding on this!

Thank you - we look forward to hearing from you and having another furbaby united with a furever family!

animal.description:
Buddy was found as a stray on a highway in early December. He has an estimated birth date of 1/7/20 and weighs 56 lbs. He was very scared and afraid of people. He is still slow to trust but is doing much better. Buddy has a very sweet and mild demeanor. He is pretty mellow overall. He is good with other dogs, kids and even cats! Once you earn his trust all he wants to do is kiss and cuddle! Buddy is a climber and can easily scale chain link or any kennel type fence. He will need a home with a 6ft privacy fence. He loves to be with his foster mom and follows her like a shadow. He is housebroken and is doing very well on his kennel training. Unfortunately, he is heartworm positive and will have to undergo treatments. His new family will need to be patient earning his trust while he adjusts to his new surroundings the first few weeks. Once he settles in and realizes he is loved you can expect a loyal, forever friend in Buddy! 

For adoption please fill out an adoption application at www.spcaeasttx.com.

animal.description:
Hi every one, my name is Big Mama and I am a large and in charge 9 year old Lab/Hound Mix. I weigh about 91 pounds, but I need to lose a little bit of this quarantine weight I’ve put on. Every one here loves me and they can’t wait for me to find a home. A senior like myself deserves all the love in the world. I am very selective with other dogs, so it might be best if I was the only one. The staff doesn’t know how I would do with cats. I can be strong on my leash when I want to sniff around and I smell something delicious or intriguing. When it comes to kids I’d prefer that they are 8+. I have the sweetest eyes and they are begging for someone to love me. I don’t like being here, but I am well behaved. I am looking for a home where I can snooze in peace and quiet and be spoiled with love. I’ve waited my whole life for a family that will love me and keep me forever. 9 years is too long to wait. Help me find that forever home.

Love, Big Mama

animal.description:
MEET BILLIE JEAN!!

Underdog Rescue does not physically have this dog in its possession. She is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A4498743.

Billie Jean is a fun, energetic girl that has been at the shelter for over 60 days and it's time for her to go home! She loves to go for a walk and walks well on the leash once she gets away from the shelter. She loves to show you how much she likes you by leaning in for pets and jumping up to show you she wants to be petted. That's where Billie Jean needs to learn her manners and not jump. She knows "sit" for treats and takes them gently so she's a smart girl and she can be trained. Billie Jean would do well in a home with a yard so she can do the zoomies back and forth. But, she's also happy to have some down time and will crawl in your lap for some nap time. The shelter staff has recommended that she be the only dog in the home because she is reactive to other dogs when she sees them. She would probably not do well in a dog park. Because of her energy, she should go to a home with older children.

If you think Billie Jean could be the dog you've been looking for, please come and meet her today!! She would love to find a home soon.

If you are interested in saving this pet, please reach out via this link: https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/foster/BPAZ/Dog

To actually visit with this pup, please make an appointment here: https://mcaccappointments.as.me/adopt. NOTE: People who sign up for these appointments often no-show, and we have seen that you can generally show up and let them know you are there to meet this particular dog and the shelter will squeeze you in, except from 12-3PM or closer to the 6PM closing time. (Please know this is not a guarantee). If the dog is at risk, please ask for a supervisor to meet that particular dog.

*Please Note: This animal is courtesy posted for the Maricopa County Shelter; UNDERDOG RESCUE DOES NOT HAVE THIS DOG. MCACC is located at 2500 S. 27th Avenue, Phoenix. Different adoption fees/policy may apply. Please visit MCACC's website http://www.maricopa.gov/pets/locations.aspx for hours. You may also wish to call 602-506-7387 (PETS) and provide the animal's A# above to verify is still available.

animal.description:
Hi I'm Sammy! 
I'm a sweet and friendly tripod little girl who loves to  run all the time. I don't need a fourth leg to keep up with and out run you, I'm great at it ?

I'm wonderful with kids 2-20 and I haven't met any babies yet but my foster mom thinks I'd do just fine. I sleep in my kennel all night and I'm learning to walk on my leash really well! 
I can get a little noisy when I'm bored or I want you to pay attention to me, but a few pets and I'm calmed right down. I love other dogs and  want to play with all of them, but I do have a prey instinct so cats and small fluffy dogs might remind me too much of a rabbit. 

I'm learning to sit and lay with my sister pup and mom thinks I'll be very easy to train- she says I'm brilliant!

I would be best in a home with a large fenced in yard where I can run to my hearts continent, and with a family who spends a lot of time either at home or places I can go too! If you would like to meet Sammy please fill out an application at

www.lowridersofthewest.org

Sammy’s adoption fee is $375.00 - she is spayed, up to date on all his vaccinations and chipped.

animal.description:
To be considered for adopting a dog from Canine Lifeline, you must have an approved application must be on file. Please visit http://www.caninelifeline.org/adoption-process/ for more information about our adoption process and to submit an online application.

Meet Jack, a very handsome and well-mannered 8 year-old Shepherd/Cattle Dog mix neutered male who was surrendered to a county dog shelter when his owner could no longer care for him. Apparently, his family now has a 6 month-old baby who was making Jack very nervous so they no longer wanted him in their home. Jack is a nice dog who is looking for a mature, quiet home without any young children so he can relax and enjoy his life. He walks very nicely on a leash for a big guy and knows some commands including sit and shake hands. He will shake with one paw and then give you the other when you ask for it! Jack isn't a fan of his crate so perhaps had never been crate-trained in the past but he does keep it clean so may be housetrained although we can't guarantee it. He would make a great companion for a retired person or couple who wants a dog who'll walk right into their house and make himself at home. Jack would love to have his humans around much of the time so his crate time would be minimal. Jack weighs about 66 pounds and his adoption fee is $200. He's neutered, heartworm negative and on monthly preventative, up to date on vaccinations including bivalent canine influenza, wormed, on flea and tick preventative, and microchipped. As part of the adoption process, all adopters must commit to a two-week adjustment period to make sure it's a great match before the adoption is finalized. Please email info@caninelifeline.org if you're interested in Jack. An approved application is required before we schedule meets with any of our dogs. Please note that we don't place our dogs in homes with children under 7 years of age. We correspond via email so please check your junkmail or spam folder to make sure our reply hasn't landed in there. Please visit our website at www.caninelifeline.org to see more photos of Jack and to submit an online application if you live in Northeast OH.

animal.description:
MEET JILLIE!!

Underdog Rescue does not physically have this dog in its possession. She is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A4522655.

Jillie is a young, beautiful girl that is at the shelter with her best friend Jenny (A4523835) and she doesn't know why she is there. She's so confused and scared. She won't walk on a leash but the kennel staff took her out to the play yard and she was cautious at first but when Jenny came out to the yard too, Jillie perked up and was very happy. You can tell that these two lived together and they love each other. Once they could see and play with each other, Jillie walked up to the staff person and play bowed and wanted to be petted.

Jenny and Jillie don't have to be adopted together, however, wouldn't it be a great ending to their story to find a home together? Because they are so timid, the shelter recommends that they go to a home with no children and the whole family should come and meet them before they are adopted. Can you give one or both of these pups a loving home? If you can, please come and meet them today!

Chuck is 2 1/2 month old male puppy that will be joining AHR from our partner rescue shelter in Louisiana.  He will be arriving with his siblings Jenny, Blair and Serena D.  He weighs approximately 10 lbs.  

He is a chill dude and the little chunk of the group.  He plays for short spurts of time but honestly just wants to be napping somewhere, all of the other siblings, will be playing and you can find chucky napping under a couch, next to you, or on a bed somewhere, extremely smart… will nap at the foot of the food bin around meal time to wait for food


Adoption fees cover age specific vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip, heartworm/lyme/ehrlichia test, worming and transport fees. 

Adoption fees: 
Through 6 months of age $450; 
7 months to through 5 years $400; 
6 years and under 9 years $325: bonded pairs are $500; 
9 years and older $250: bonded pairs are $300 

FOR PUPPIES: PLEASE READ!!
Homes considering Puppies must be prepared for:
Flexible Schedules for Potty Training. Puppies can only hold urine for one hour per month of age. Crate Training for the next 10 months to keep them safe from chewing on everything in your home. Supervision with Children and Obedience training. 
Socialization; both with new people, children and other dogs outside of the home.
Homes that want a well behaved dog, must be prepared to put the time, effort and costs associated to train a puppy. Well behaved dogs are not born, they are trained!  Please do not apply for a puppy if you cannot or do not have the time for a puppy.

Almost Home Rescue of New England is a 501 c 3 non-profit rescue; rescuing dogs since 2005. All Adoption applications are completed on line at www.almosthomerescue.net 

This dog is available unless it is marked as Pending, meaning Pending Adoption. This dog is in foster care locally, ONLY if Maine or New Hampshire is listed next to the dogs name; otherwise, the dog is still waiting with our partner rescue for an adoption or foster home in New England. 

PLEASE NOTE - We will check your veterinary reference, to ensure that current and prior dogs have a history of being kept up to date on rabies and distemper, have had annual heartworm tests, and are on heartworm preventative at least 6 months of the year. Current pets must by spayed/neutered. 

Imported dogs are transported on a USDA approved transport with a Health Certificate. All imported dogs are quarantined 14 days prior to getting on transport.

animal.description:
One handsome dude, right? Buck came to us from another shelter where he had arrived as a stray, so sadly we don't know anything about his background. Nor, can we say with any certainty what kind of mix he might be - perhaps hound and maybe shepherd? 

We're estimating him to be between 3 and maybe five years old.  He really enjoys his time outdoors so would love a quieter home with active adults or perhaps one with older teens.   He really enjoys his walks and walks well on a leash. A perfect day for Buck would start with a long walk or maybe a run in the morning, followed by or perhaps before that a great breakfast, an afternoon nap, another good walk or time exploring his fenced yard, a good dinner and then a long snooze in front of the woodstove.  

Buck can be a bit aloof when meeting new people and in fact, may be somewhat protective of those he considers family.  He probably prefers to be your only canine companion.  He's the kind of guy who strikes you as being wise waaay beyond his years when he looks at you with those deep brown eyes.  

When Buck came to us he tested positive for heart worm and has subsequently undergone all the heart worm treatment.  Consequently, he's been with us for several months on strict crate rest while he recovered from the treatments. That was tough for  a big active guy.  He is now ready for the next adventure. and is waiting patiently for someone to share that with.

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Harrison! I'm a 2-year-old male Treeing Walker Coonhound mix who is searching for my forever family! It took me a little while to really settle in at my foster home but now I'm really letting my goofy and loving personality shine. I like to play with toys and kick all of my foster mom's couch cushions on the floor while I do it. I love to wrestle with my foster brother, he's a hound too, and when he doesn't feel like playing with me I bark right in his face. I love to look out the window and make sure everyone knows when any people or animals walk past. I'm working on my manners and walking on a leash without pulling. My foster mom says when I'm properly motivated, I pick things up really fast! I get along well with humans and dogs and have even lived with a cat, but I shouldn't live with young children. I'm a medium energy guy, I'm house trained, and I love to be involved in everything you're doing. Can we be best friends forever?
You can watch for stories, pictures and videos about me on our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/groups/40103261297/
 
Adoption fee: $375.00
 
Adoption fees for all dogs/puppies include a $50 refundable training deposit. Complete your basic training program and provide a copy of the certificate within 4 months (120 days) of adoption and we will refund $50 of the original adoption fee.
 
All dogs/puppies have been fully vetted including spay/neuter, micro-chipping, worming, heartworm testing and preventative treatment, flea/tick preventative, and all required age appropriate vaccinations. As required by Wisconsin Act 90, all dogs will have received a veterinarian exam (CVI) within the past 30 days.
 
Our adoption process requires the submission of an application. Applications and Adoption Rules can be found on our website, on the "HOW TO ADOPT" tab at JRsPupsNStuff.org. Upon receipt of the completed application, we will process the application including: contact with your veterinarian and completion of a home visit. Please be sure to include the contact information for your vet as we will call. If your vet requires an information release, please be sure to contact them as soon as you submit your application. We are a group of volunteers with families and jobs, so please be patient and allow a few days for our response.
 
JR's Pups-N-Stuff Dog Sellers License 270089-DS

All dogs/puppies have been fully vetted including spay/neuter, micro-chipping, worming, heartworm testing and preventative treatment, flea/tick preventative, and all required age appropriate vaccinations. As required by Wisconsin Act 90, all dogs will have received a veterinarian exam (CVI) within the past 30 days.
 
Our adoption process requires the submission of an application. Applications and Adoption Rules can be found on our website, on the "HOW TO ADOPT" tab at JRsPupsNStuff.org. Upon receipt of the completed application, we will process the application including: contact with your veterinarian and completion of a home visit. Please be sure to include the contact information for your vet as we will call. If your vet requires an information release, please be sure to contact them as soon as you submit your application. We are a group of volunteers with families and jobs, so please be patient and allow a few days for our response.
 
JR's Pups-N-Stuff Dog Sellers License 270089-DS

animal.description:
Hogan, our miracle boy, is recovering and getting around well. He is sweet, quiet, loving and so pleased to finally be safe and warm. He can now sleep with both eyes closed! He gets along with other dogs. He is such a good looking boy!

He's ready for his forever family. He a tripod Vizsla mix who has been friendly with any dog or person he met. He will make someone a best friend and is low energy. 

Hogan had not lived the life of a loved family member. He was untrusting of humans and human touch. He escaped from a small rural shelter, lived as a stray for over a month and during that time got hit by a car. His leg was mangled and infected. In addition, his spleen had a tumor on it and fluid surrounding his organs and some sort of obstruction. The injuries were severe and infection had set in. So much needed to be done and worry was whether he could make it through any surgery. After much debate, they went in...his spleen was removed, his leg amputated and they did exploratory surgery. He had a long road ahead of him but he made it!

animal.description:
JTs Have It All, R 77G, L 70692

Hey, I'm Have It! I'm a sensitive girl who is still adjusting to retired life. I really like cuddles, scritches and hugs, but also doing my own thing - sometimes I'll just nap in a different room or go to my crate for some alone time. Right now I still think breakfast should happen at 5 am, but I'll go back to sleep if you feed me and let me out! I get along with all the people I've met, but haven't met any kids. I got a little scared of a small dog, although eventually I walked within four feet of him! I did chase the resident cat once, but when I got scolded I didn't want to be anywhere near him, so we'll have to see if I ignore him now or if I'll get the courage to chase him again! I would rather not leave my safe, warm home right now, so I don't let us take very long walks and I'm much quicker when we turn towards home! Sometimes I try every path, in case it's the one to our house. I need a family that will help me build confidence and experience a lot of things!

animal.description:
JD Ascension, R 18A, L 71696Hi there, I'm Scion! I'm a gentle boy who is quickly turning into a snuggle-bug! I enjoy all kinds of hugs and snuggles. I like going on walks, although my feet get cold quickly. I'm super eager to meet all the dogs and people we see outside! Ironically, I'm a bit shy when I finally get a chance to meet those new people. Loud noises still scare me, and I'm a little bit stubborn so it takes a little work to get me to move along, but eventually I do. I would rather not go outside even to potty by myself, and if I am alone I make it super quick! I currently live with a feline housemate, and I still think it's really fun to chase but I'm slowly learning. I have a little bit of a stubborn streak, but treats are helping. I do spend time in my kennel, but only with treats to lure me in and I still spend a little time whining about it!

(Littermate to Justin)

To see other hounds currently in our care please visit the Hounds in Our Care page on our website.

You can also learn learn more about our adoption philosophy and find a link to our online application at our website: www.gpa-mn.org

Hi there, I'm Justin! I'm a big, sweet boy, and when I say big I mean it! Bruno lives life large!!! At about three years old, he's really still a lot like a puppy! He has an incredibly adventurous and fun loving spirit and is up for just about anything!  With boundless energy and stamina, he promises to be a great hiking companion, running buddy or happy to accompany you on just about any activity you're into!   

Bruno is a sweet guy with a friendly disposition.  He loves everyone he meets and seems to enjoy the company of other canine friends.  He really just wants to love and be loved.  Bruno could benefit from some formal training, working on his leash manners and a bit more focus, but he promises to be a willing student.  So, if you're looking for a good buddy to share in your adventures, Bruno just may  be your guy! 

Adoption Fee: $175  (dogs over 1 year) or $225 (dogs under 1 year) includes spay/neuter rabies, DHLPP and kennel cough vaccinations, worming, flea treatment, heartworm testing, heartworm preventative, microchipping and microchip registration fee.

Or, call us at 607-594-2255, Ext. 201 to set up an appointment at another time. Visit us on line at www.schuylerhumane.org for additional information, an adoption application, to see more adoptable dogs and cats or for directions to our shelters.

animal.description:
DOB: 2/22/2014
40lbs

We are currently accepting applications to adopt Newton. If you are interested in meeting and adopting him, please submit an adoption application by visiting our website (www.HarborOfHopeDogRescue.org). Due to COVID19 safety measures, meetings are currently only being scheduled with approved adopters.

Cute, affectionate, and WICKED smart..thats Newton in a nutshell! If dogs had IQ scores, Newton would be considered exceptionally gifted. He currently lives with 5 other dogs and does well with both male and female companions. Despite being a heeler, he isnt tremendously mouthy, so would do well with kids. 

This boy does have a bit of a stubborn streak (he is part heeler afterall!), so he will need an owner who is committed to continuing his current training plan. This includes setting healthy boundaries, giving him plenty of mental exercise learning new commands and tricks and taking him for walks to work his brain and body. He does incredible on a leash and is not reactive to other people or dogs while out and about. If youre looking for an outstanding companion who will adore you and will always make life exciting, Newton may be the dog for you!

All of our dogs are fully vetted before adoption, including vaccinations, spay/neuter, and a microchip.

The adoption process consists of an online application, a vet reference, two personal references, and a home visit. If approved to adopt, there is an adoption contract and an adoption amount. The adoption amount for Newton is $300 and goes toward the vetting and care of all the dogs in our rescue.

All adoptions will take place in the Omaha NE area and must be done in person. We are willing to adopt to out-of-state applicants, contingent on our ability to complete a home visit, but you must be willing to come to the Omaha area to complete the adoption. We do not ship, transport or deliver our dogs.

If you would like to learn more about Harbor of Hope Dog Rescue, please visit our website (www.HarborOfHopeDogRescue.org) or our Facebook page. Thank you for your support!

animal.description:
Sky, Pit Mix, 2 years, 53 lbs,
This sweet girl found her way to a rural shelter after someone in her family developed a bad allergy to dogs. We took her in and are determined to find her a new home! Sky is extra snuggly and super playful! She loves flopping on your lap and chewing on a toy. She gets along well with other dogs and follows all the play rules. This cutie is good in a crate and even hangs out in there when she’s not asked to. She’s also great with kids!

Sky is working on leash training (she is very strong) and learning how to respect people’s personal space (she likes to lick faces and jump a bit). She needs a home without cats.

See more of her personality on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/skysofly614/

Requirements for Adoption:
Sorry but we only place our dogs in the Columbus area.  For rescues/shelters across Ohio, visit:  ColumbusDogConnection.com/RescuesShelters.html
Must be over the age of 24 to adopt.
Your resident pets must be spayed/neutered.

Adoption Process:
We do not have an application. Adoptions are pet-adopter driven.
To meet our pets:
Call our office at 614-471-9000 or click on the pet which you are interested in and send email. We will be happy to discuss the adoption process with you and set-up a visit at time of contact. The foster dogs are in foster homes and most of the cats reside at our office.

The adoption process includes a lease manager reference (if applicable) , a veterinarian reference, a home-visit (in-person or virtual).
If you've never owned a pet, part of our adoption process requires that you call several vet offices to compare services, prices, and availability. 
Questions to ask include:
How many doctors are at your practice?
Can I request to see a specific Vet or would I be scheduled with first available?
What are your hours?
How much is:   annual exam, heartworm test & tablets, an x-ray,  vaccines, a non-emergency office call? 
Do you recommend vaccines every year or every three years?  (every 3 yrs as suggested by the AVMA)           

The pooches that visit your home will not be left there at the end of the visit. We take them back home with us so your family can discuss to ensure he/she is a good fit for your home.

There is an adoption agreement and adoption fees as follows:
 $300 for Adult Dogs (6yrs  & younger)
 $200 for Senior Dogs (7 yrs and older)
 $80 for Cats  

 All pets are spayed/neutered, up-to-date on vaccinations, heartworm tested (dogs), fiv/leukemia tested (cats), & micro-chipped.
Known medical conditions are discussed at time of inquiry.

animal.description:
Hey all you Harry Potter Fansyou will be excited to know that Boston Buddies has our very own Alastor "Mad Eye" Moody. He came to us late last year from the Carson Shelter and got his name because of his little shrunken eye. We took him to the eye doctor who confirmed his little eye was not visual. He does see out of his other eye but there is some scar tissue from an old injury so he will continue to need lubricating eye drops to keep it feeling comfortable. Once this Wizard worked a little magic and lost some much needed weight he was ready for a full makeover. He had surgery to remove that little eye, the family jewels and a couple bad teeth and drank a magic potion (Panacur & Metronidazole) to rid him of any pesky parasites. Alastor is estimated to be 8 years old and currently weighs 27 lbs. Wish we knew more about his previous life because it seems that living with muggles is totally new for him. Any time he is faced with something he is unsure of he just "freezes". Maybe he thinks he is wearing a coat of invisibility? Or maybe he just thinks if he remains totally still no one will know he is there? You can't help but fall in love with this quirky guy. Leash walks are a work in progress. He uses the doggie door to go outside to potty but take him out the front door with a harness and leash to go on a walk and he digs his heels in and won't move an inch. Mr. Moody enjoys the company of other dogs and bootie scratches from his humans. He is great for baths and nail trims. Initially, Alastor would "mark" in the house but since being neutered that unattractive behavior has subsided. Alastor "Mad Eye" Moody is up to date on his vaccines, microchipped and ready to add a little magic to your life. If you want to make 2021 and beyond more mystical and incredible than you could ever imagine, you should fly on over to our website and complete an adoption application for Alastor Moody -
https://www.bostonbuddies.org/adoption-application/

Adoption Donation is $300.00

View more pictures on our facebook page https://www.facebook.com/BostonBuddiesInc

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Charlei, and I know the spelling of my name is wrong, but that is what it is. I tell everyone its Old English, for Charlie. I need a new home. You see my mom did something really bad. She has kids! All was great before, so now I am acting up as there are now TWO of them invading my peaceful home. I am a very lucky fellow as I had some great years, now it's gone. I need a get out of jail card now!!! As you can see I am real cute and a great guy at 6 years old. I need a new home as an only dog. A single guy or gal would be grand as I like to protect my owners from interlopers. I am a big guy of unknown Westie mix gene pool and I weigh in at approx 40 lbs. Yep, That right, I am extra large so there is more to love. Sunshine State Westie Rescue - Florida folks have told me that they will find a new home for me, which turned out to be the luckiest thing of all this mess. They promised to take really good care of me and pick out only the right home. I am with my original owners as my home gets lined up. So HURRY up and pick me! The Westie Rescue-Florida lady wants to tell you some more stuff, but I can't wait to meet you and come live with you forever. XOXO, Charlei Please take a few minutes and go to the website http://westierescue.com/. Take a look at the Frequently Asked Questions to familiarize yourself with all the factors affecting your decision to adopt a rescued westie like Charlei.

If you think you could be the perfect forever home for a rescued Florida westie, please fill out and submit the Adoption Application. PLEASE MAKE CERTAIN TO FILL OUT EVERYTHING COMPLETELY. The incomplete applications are filed until someone has time to get back to them, which unfortunately, in an all volunteer organization, could take quite a while.

When your finished, send an email to: aggie.sswr@gmail.com to let her know you are interested in my big butt. She will smile and say "Congrats".

ASK ABOUT CHARLEI (FLORIDA)

It takes anywhere between 3-7 days to process an application - the more complete the application the easier it is for us to process it. Please notify your vet that we will be contacting them and to release information to us.

3. Invitation thru email to meet the dog(s).

4. Adoption Contract

animal.description: Benny is a 1-2 yr old Boxer mix, whom was found to have heartworms when he came to us. He has had treatment for the heartworms but will need to continue on monthly heartworm preventative for the rest of his life. He has been retested on 1/21/21 and that test was negative. Benny likes to give gentle kisses. He will stay next to his person without being called. Benny is mellow most of the time but will have bursts of energy. He pulls on a leash but with some basic obedience training, this could easily be resolved. Benny is food motivated. He knows the sit command. Benny is intensely interested in cats in a shelter atmosphere. Dogs are generally tested with dogs of their own size; and dog meets with the resident dogs are always encouraged. Our cat test should be used as a general purpose screening only to rule out overt aggression; we always recommend caution when introducing dogs to cats in the home. Recommendation on suitability of placement with children by their ages is based on behavioral observations including energy level and response to body handling. We never recommend leaving young children unsupervised with dogs, and we cannot guarantee the behavior of dogs with children, other pets or cats. Behavior evaluations should be considered as a snapshot of the behavior of the dog at this point in time; JHS believes all dog families need to be prepared to invest time and energy into training as well as provide common sense management of their new dog. We always encourage family to do some research on the breeds or mixes of breeds prior to adoption as many can have some unique characteristics that may or may not fit into their families. Always remember that the majority of dogs at our shelter have been exposed to or may have kennel cough. Kennel cough is contagious to other dogs, please talk to your vet if you have any questions about kennel cough prior to adoption. Please ask your adoption counselor at time of adoption if you have any unanswered questions regarding illnesses and treatments of the path that you are adopting. For more information about this dog or any others at our Shelter, please visit www.joplinhumane.org. We are the Joplin Humane Society in Joplin, Missouri. 417-623-3642

animal.description:
Please read the dog's entire bio before you apply.  Sadly, we are no longer able to respond to every application, but will contact the one that is a good match within 3 days.
Jacob is a male 15 lb chubby chihuahua, he is very chubby and should be closer to 12 lbs.   He was born 1/2012.   He is super sweet once he warms up to you, but is cautious for the first 10-15 min.  Probably not ideal with small children.   He is quiet and crate trained and good on the leash on a harness.  He likes other dogs and is very cute with the best colors and a cute face with blue eyes.   He does have a small "cherry eye" on one of his eyes, but since its not bothering him, has been there a very long time and is very small, we are opting not to put him through surgery.
Most of our dogs are not available to an out of the area adoption because of difficulty to follow up.  If you do not live within a 2 hr drive of Orange County, please email us before applying to see if the dog you are interested is may be a candidate for long distance adoption.    We only make consider long distance adoptions for dogs who have been in our rescue for 6 plus months with no local candidates.
If you are interested in adopting one of our rescues, please visit our main website for adoption procedures at www.pupsandpals.net and then fill out our application.  Please note that we are all volunteers so it may take up to 3 days to process your application, but you will hear back from us if your application is a good match for the pet. 
We do not have a shelter so individual appointments must be made to meet the pet you are interested in.  Our pets are fostered/boarded all over LA and Orange County.  
This pet is altered, vaccinated, microchipped, and has had a brief temperament evaluation to help us determine what type of  a home he/she would thrive in.  Please note that we put lots of time and effort to make sure our pets are ready to be someone's perfect pet before they go home.... and to make sure that we will have the best possible match for this pet we do require an : application, interview, adoption fee and in some case a home check.  
Listed for adoption: 1/12/2021
Adoption fee: $300
PLEASE DO NOT call or email to see if a pet is available.  We update our pages daily so if he/she is pictured here in the available dogs section, we are accepting applications at this time.

animal.description:
Hey, y’all! My name is Dioja, but everyone calls me Hoss. I came to TIRR Rescue in late 2020.

I have some separation anxiety, and my family wasn’t quite sure how to handle it. I was my mom’s constant shadow and panicked whenever she wasn’t around. My parents finally decided it was best for everyone if they let TIRR Rescue find a home that was better able to handle me.

I’m a VERY sweet boy and I like just about everyone I meet. However, just like with my mom, I’ll pick a person and stick to them like glue. If I can see them nearby, I’ll cry and whine until I can get out and be right next to them. I have no idea just how big I am, and I can cause quite a bit of damage when I’m panic, so it’s important that I find a family who knows how to handle separation anxiety or is willing to keep me with them all the time. I would also do best in an active family; I like going for daily walks (or jogs)!

If you think you might be my forever family, be sure to contact my rescue people!

~~~~

PERSONALITY:
Dioja is a super sweet boy who has some separation anxiety. While he likes just about everyone he meets, he will pick one person and stick to them like glue. He tends to panic when he’s not around them. He’s a large, active boy who will need an active family that will keep him busy to help him with his anxiety. While Dioja’s association with other animals is still under review, he is very much a ladies’ man and loves cuddling and getting belly scratches.

~~~~

For more information on Dioja, please visit tirrrescue.org/dioja.

animal.description: In Greek mythology, Apollo is the ultimate well-rounded man, the god of archery, music and dance, healing and diseases, truth and prophecy, the sun and light, poetry and more. Well our buddy Apollo is also incredibly well-rounded. Apollo is a sweet, handsome boy. He's easy to leash up and handle and takes treats gently. Apollo was found as a stray, but he spent time in a foster home where he was on his very best behavior. In his foster home, Apollo learned to be crate-trained, but he most enjoyed sleeping on the couch. He's housetrained and loves to play fetch with tennis balls or tug with a rope toy. His foster family tells us he was a good and friendly boy and the perfect houseguest, but they brought him back when they realized they didn't have enough time to spend with him. Apollo is a very good boy and he'd love to get out of the shelter and into a home. He would like to meet any resident dogs to make sure it's a good fit, and is looking for a home with no cats. If he sounds like your type of pup, make an appointment to meet him today. animal.description:
My name is really Maggie, but my foster family calls me Big Mama. I am about 50 pounds and I don't like to talk about my age (but if you must know, I am about 3). My life with AAP started after I was picked up as a pregnant stray with horrible skin and missing part of my tail. I don't like to admit that I was also a bit shy. I am much more comfortable in my skin these days (literally and figuratively) and am glad to be a proper house dog. It is amazing what some good food and a warm bed can do for a soul! And a bath, too. I'm not a big fan, but I will tolerate it. Something I will not tolerate, though, are cats. They get on my nerves! And if they run it is game on! I was a really good mom to my pups. I had a litter of 10! That's why my foster family calls me Big Mama. Don't let my size fool you, I have a big personality and lots of love to give. I know my puppies will be in good hands with AAP and will find great homes, but right now I am looking forward to finding a forever home for myself. Big Mama's adoption fee is $175. She is up to date on age appropriate vaccinations, spayed, and microchipped.
All of our dogs are spayed or neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccinations, microchipped and if over 6 months of age, heartworm tested and on heartworm preventative in their foster home.

We require an approved application to meet any of our dogs. We do not have a shelter location and will not arrange a meeting without an approved application.

We strive to make sure the bios provided for our dogs are complete and accurate; we do understand that mistakes happen, however, so if you absolutely cannot find the answer to your question in the dog's bio, you can contact us for more information.

We require a home visit for each dog we adopt out, so we adopt within a 2 hour radius of Dayton, OH. If you are outside of this radius, we encourage you to contact your local rescue or shelter.

animal.description: Where do we start with  Esperanza?  A good Samaritan spotted this gal under an over-pass exit ramp.  It took the help of Maricopa County Animal Control to catch her.  Espi was in dire need of medical help.  She had numerous  large and infected mammary gland tumors, was skin and bones and terrified.  Espi under went major surgery and the vet not only removed the large tumors that lined her belly, we also learned that her uterus was stretched and torn beyond recognition.   It has been nearly four months since this gal has been in our care and we feel it is time for Espi to continue her journey.  Espi will need to find a  loving, understanding family that has a quiet routine so she can continue to gain confidence.  Espi does enjoy the company of other dogs and we feel she can learn from them.  Mostly, she still needs time to warm up to people and settle into a routine that will allow her to trust.  Espi is currently with her foster family and is becoming quite the couch potato.  She increasingly enjoys human touch and loves to be in the company of humans.   It is the quick movements, loud noises that will startle her. We think Espi will do great with a family that has kids, other animals but also allows her time to continue to heal.  A consistent routine will benefit Espi.  She will no doubt make a sweet, sweet companion.  We estimate Espi to be about three years old, she is slight dog, about 40lbs.  She is very sweet and has paid her dues.  She deserves to be spoiled every single day she is on this earth.  If you are interested in giving Esperanza the best home in the world, please take a moment to fill out an application: https://www.povertyspets.org/adoption-form .  You will be contacted within 48-72 hours.  $200 adoption donation.

animal.description:
To be considered for adopting a dog from Canine Lifeline, you must have an approved application must be on file. Please visit http://www.caninelifeline.org/adoption-process/ for more information about our adoption process and to submit an online application.

Dorian is a handsome 2 year-old Black Lab mix who's short, stocky, and a solid 57 pounds. He was found as a stray and taken to an overcrowded county dog shelter. When he wasn't claimed there, he made the trip to Canine Lifeline so he could take his time finding the perfect new home. Dorian seems to enjoy meeting new people and has done well with everyone he's met since coming to us. He has also been fine with female dogs but has been a little growly with other males. That is likely to tone down now that he's neutered. Overall, he's a gentle boy who walks quite nicely on a leash, has excellent crate manners, and may be housetrained too although we can't guarantee that. Dorian is happy to have a tennis ball to play with so might be a good fetcher with a little more practice. He was very well-mannered when his photos were taken and was interested in the squeaky toys we used to get his attention. Dorian is very food-motivated and eager to please so it should be a pleasure to work with him on obedience training. His adoption fee is $350. He's neutered, heartworm negative and on monthly preventative, up to date on vaccinations including bivalent canine influenza, wormed, on flea and tick preventative, and microchipped. As part of the adoption process, all adopters must commit to a two-week adjustment period to make sure it's a great match before the adoption is finalized. Please email info@caninelifeline.org if you're interested in Dorian. An approved application is required before we schedule meets with any of our dogs. Please note that we don't place our dogs in homes with children under 7 years of age. We correspond via email so please check your junkmail or spam folder to make sure our reply hasn't landed in there. Please visit our website at www.caninelifeline.org to see more photos of Dorian and to submit an online application if you live in Northeast OH.

animal.description:
Luna (previously Petunia) is a Great Pyrenees mix that had to come back to the shelter because she was trying to dominate the other dog in the house. She was wonderful with all the humans in the house but was miss bossy pants with the other dog. The goal in life for a Great Pyrenees is to protect livestock, children, people, grass, flowers. lawn furniture, bird feeders, the moon, and any other real or imaginary predators that may intrude on your personal space,  She is about 1 year 3 months old and has been spayed, fully vaccinate, blood tested and microchipped. 

She is affectionate, but not needy.
She is a huge alarm barker! If she hears something, she barks, a lot!
She is fearful of strangers but warms up after 10-15 minutes.
When she is worried, she get close by your side. She is insecure.
She is super playful.
She knows paw and sit.
She doesn't seem to be a fan of cats.
She is very dog selective.

Lunas ideal home should be:
A house and NOT an apartment. Apartment living for Petunia may not be ideal because of her barking.
Experience and an understanding of working dogs is required. Luna needs a job and will need a large amount of exercise not only for her body, but for her brain.
Older kids (8+), because the young ones may just be
too scary for her and she can be like a bull in a china shop.
Enrolling her in obedience classes IS REQUIRED for adoption. Proof of enrollment is required. Training not only will this help forge a lasting bond with Luna, it will help her to be a better pet.

If you fit the bill and think you would be a great pet parent for Luna, please let us know. Showings are by appointment only, due to COVID. We are sending adoption applications to interested people. If your application is approved, we schedule a meet and greet appointment.
In the message box of your inquiry for Luna, please put to the attention of Adoption Counselor. 

Her adoption fee is $165.00
