animal.description:
Greetings! It's soo nice to meet you! My name is Amalea, you can call me that or Ama or Lea and I love everyone and everything. For a dog who spent much of its life as a stray I really, really adore life and everything in it. I am about 8 months old mix (Australian Kelpie looks like) and will give you a toothache is so sweet. My brother and I were both found on the street and I am overcoming being scared slowly, my family takes me on hikes and walks and I'm slowly becoming braver, another dog would definitely help with that. I love all other dogs even though I will need slow intros and time to warm up as initially I'm very defensive. I'm so sweet and submissive, all types of dogs love me once I warm up! My scars tell a very different story than I would. Before coming to 2 Blondes I got hit by a porcupine when arriving my face was pretty messed up and now it's been taken care of and I'm healing. I'm excited to start my new life getting belly rubs, cuddles and kisses all day long. I'm working hard on sit and other manners. I definitely have some herding breed in me as I'm VERY mouthy at this time small children would not be good for me as I bite to show my love. I will sleep in the kennel at night but I don't go in willingly, I am about 99% potty trained, I know sit and my family is slowly working on other skills. I enjoy all toys including the puzzle ones, mom says since I've got some herding breed is very smart. I really want to be the best girl and I am looking for my furever home to show me that chance! As my face is still healing I may not be available immediately, but am still available for meet and greets!

Adoption fee includes the following:


	Spay/Neuter
	Rabies Vaccination
	Distemper / Parvo Vaccines (includes series of 3 for puppies)
	Bordetella
	Microchip with prepaid lifetime registration
	Deworming

animal.description:
Sig

Currently in Rapid City SD 
2 year old
Olde English Bulldog (yes purebred)
GREAT with other dogs
Unknown with cats
NO CHILDREN 
House trained
Knows basic commands & crate training is unknown but he is NOT destructive 
Has nipped/bit twice when startled 
Fully vetted
60lbs approx

This sweet boy is a ham and a total delight but unfortunately when startled he bites. He has done this twice, once when the fedex man came and once with the toddler, in both situations he was asleep and was startled awake. Both broke the skin but didn't require medical attention. His family has spoken about euthanizing him but instead they are willing to allow us to step in and help. We need a foster or adoptive home willing to work with him to feel safe. We will also get his hearing checked to make sure there isn't an impairment that is also attributing to the situation. 

Will have a behavioral waiver

Due to his predominant breed being an English Bulldog we are seeking an adopter with BRACHYCEPHALIC BREED EXPERIENCE. Further all our brachycephalic dogs MUST vet at an AAHA certified vet, this is because of their extreme vet needs. Brachycephalic dogs are extremely expensive dogs to upkeep so please bare that in mind when applying and make sure you're in a financial place to take it on.

 

 $400.00 Adoption Fee 

(Which is considered a non refundable donation and being we are a 501c3 organization it is tax deductible. The fee itself is not negotiable, our vets don't negotiate and thus neither do we.)

If you can help please contact us ASAP!

To Contact Us

Message us through our website http://www.highplainspaw.org

Message the Facebook Page at https://www.facebook.com/HighPlainsPAW

Fill out our Adoption Application at https://www.highplainspaw.org/adoption-application

Fill out our Foster Application at https://www.highplainspaw.org/foster-application

Email us at highplainspaw@gmail.com

Call our VOICEMAIL at (402)957-1578

WE DO NOT HAVE A FACILITY ALL OUR DOGS ARE LOCATED IN FOSTER HOMES. This means there is no place for you to go in person to view our dogs. We ask that an application be filled out and we will go from there!

animal.description:
*No Large dogs
**Small young playful dog needed**
*cats okay
*Kids over 8 yrs of age 
*high energy
*No apartments/rented rooms 
*must have attached secured yard 


Hi my name is Bonnie. My foster family lovingly calls me Bonnie Roo because when I get excited or happy my bark sounds like rooster roo-ing! 

I’m a young girl (about one year of age) and I’m pretty petite, and weigh only 7 lbs.  

My friends at Rhodie’s Rescue saved me when they were notified by a property owner that I was living in a pipe. I don’t know how I ended up there, but I was so terrified and cold I was shaking bad and I was starving cause I hadn’t eaten in a while....my bones were showing everywhere. As soon as they caught me and brought me home, I felt safe and I got to eat really good food! My bones are no longer showing and I don’t even think about my ‘past life’ anymore! I’m having way to much fun in my foster home! 
 I Love other small dogs and will play all day with them. I really want to have a young, friendly and playful small doggie in my new home so we can play and have fun together. 
I like the cats in my foster home and try to play with them so if you have a cat(s) I hope they are dog friendly. 
I’m always on the go, play play play, then eat and back to play!  
I absolutely LOVE toys! I play tug-of-war, and if you throw balls 
I’ll go run to pick them up but, I won’t bring them back to you! LOL  
I’ll jump up on your lap for a little cuddles then off I go
I’m full of energy so another little doggie to play with will be ideal. 

I’m still working on house training and getting the hang of it, but I still have accidents. 
I’m learning to walk on a leash but will need continued training... I’m very scared on the leash so my foster Mom has been working with me just in the house and yard. 
I sleep quietly in my crate at night. 
I’d love to have a gentle family and playful doggie friend to call my own! 
My adoption fee is $300 which includes health examination, current vaccinations, spay, microchip, along with any other medical or dental deemed necessary by our veterinarian.

animal.description:
Pepper is a happy and friendly 11 month old boy who would love a family of his own. He was rescued from Texas, where there is an overwhelming number of homeless pets, with limited resources to help them. Pepper is an active boy who loves to play. He is friendly and outgoing with everyone he meets. 

Please fill out the adoption application at https://snarrnortheast.org/ if you are interested in adopting Pepper. 

-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING
-------------------------------------------------------
**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES: $495 for puppies / $375 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary

She is friendly with everyone she meets. She loves to play ball and loves attention. She has a cute short and stocky body. **PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING**

If you are interested in adopting any of the puppies, our adoption fee is $495 ( puppies) $375 (adults) which includes transportation from the South and we do suggest putting a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several littermates.

**Please understand that we are a volunteer based organization. While our volunteers try to answer all emails/questions as quickly as possible, below please find answers to some of our most frequently asked questions. We ask that you please read these FAQ's to see if your question has already been answered before emailing additional questions:

- If a dog or puppy is listed on Petfinder, they are still available. Please do not email asking if they are still available. If a dog or puppy is still listed, then we are still accepting applications :-) We do not go on a first come first serve basis, but on best fit for the family and most importantly, the puppy or dog.

- We are taking our best guess on breed and size when fully-grown (or already an adult), based on the puppy's/dog’s physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. We rarely are able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. 

- Our dogs/puppies are either at our Adoption Center in Brewster, NY, in foster care, or are adopted straight from transport. An application is necessary to meet any dog/puppy. Often, dogs and puppies are spoken for before they arrive. Many people feel more comfortable with a meet and greet which we completely understand and respect, however please know you are taking a chance of that puppy/dog getting adopted by someone else before hand.

- The way to start the process for any dog or puppy is by filling out an application. Applications for foster or adoption can be found at www.snarrnortheast.org and by clicking either adopt or foster from the main menu. If you fill out an application, please make sure you answer all the questions in as much detail as possible and that you receive a confirmation email, otherwise we did NOT receive it.

animal.description:
***Meredith is available only through the Foster to Adopt Program***

Hi, my name is Meredith but you can call me sweetie because everyone says I'm so sweet. I love to greet friends at the door. I just love to see company and to be honest, I do good in anyone's arms. I just love giving hugs and have no problem putting my head on your shoulder for long periods of time. I'm good at calming you down and have no problem doing what you say. I just want to make you happy and I think you will be when you come to see me :-)

FOSTER TO ADOPT:
Meredith is Heartworm positive and is starting her Heartworm treatment. This treatment takes about 3 months with 3-5 appointments at our vets in Minnetonka. After the treatment series is completed, a heartworm test is done a month later and repeated in the months following until a negative test result is achieved. A negative result can take up to 2-9 months after treatment. During the treatment and until the test result is negative, she will need to make sure her heart rate is not elevated due to high energy play or exercise. Meredith is only available through the Foster to Adopt Program at this time. The foster to adopt commitment will be for an ADOPTION but will be actually fostering until she is cleared with a negative Heartworm test result, which at that time, we will make the adoption official. It is a program for a commitment. All of the medical expenses will be paid for by the rescue while she is in a foster to adopt home. Food, kennel, grooming and other supplies will be provided by the foster in the foster to adopt program. 

Meredith also will need to be spayed as her puppies just turned 8 weeks old and are in the process of getting adopted. The spay will happen over the next few months at the rescue's vet in Minnetonka. 

--------------------------------------------

All our Warrior Dogs will have all age appropriate medical care and vaccines, a microchip, and spay/neuter before adoption unless age is a factor with a puppy younger than 6-12 months at the time of adoption. If that is the case, the spay/neuter will be covered in the adoption fee and the owner will be responsible to have the procedure completed at a Warrior Dog Rescue Veterinarian at the appropriate time.

Please note that the majority of our dogs in rescue are from shelters where they have been found as strays or abandoned. Their breed description is based on our very best educated guess based on physical characteristics and their dispositions. If they came to our rescue as an owner surrender, the breed description will be listed as provided by the previous owner.

In early December, a Good Samaritan found this girl in the city of Fontana extremely emaciated, shut down and showing signs that she had been used for breeding.

We hustled to make a plan and scooped her up and got her right to into our vet. 

She was only 47 lbs and as we suspected, tests came back showing she was starved.

Thankfully all of her organs were still functioning at safe levels other than a UTI that we treated with antibiotics.

This 6 year old stunner is now healthy, in a loving foster home in a receiving all the love that she deserves.

She’s been assessed by our trainer, is responsive to corrections on leash. She’s curious about other dogs and walked nicely side by side on leash with another calm female her size.

She is scheduled to be spayed and microchipped in 2 weeks.

We are now accepting applications for her forever human!

If you’re interested in meeting this angel, please tap the link in our bio to fill out our adoption application.

animal.description:
IAN IS IN A FOSTER HOME

Date of birth: 10/1/2020

2/1/2021:  Ian is a super cute American Staffordshire mix pup!  He currently weighs about 20 lbs and we think he’ll weigh 50 lbs or more when fully grown.

• Ian is very energetic and loves to play!  We feel that he needs a home with another young playful dog or puppy. We’d ask you to bring your dog to meet Ian to see if they could be good buddies.  He lives with other dogs in his foster home.

• Ian will need a house with a fenced yard.

• Ian had a rough beginning. He and his mom and his brother, Fergus, were very neglected and had been wandering the streets. They were very skinny. (Fergus has an adoption pending and is scheduled to go to his new home later this week.)

• Ian can be a teeny bit timid at first, but he’s playful and fun-loving, so it doesn’t take him long at all to warm up to new people and situations.  He's also food motivated!

• Ian is just a baby, so he’ll need more work on house training and other basic training. 

• He’s been vaccinated, neutered and microchipped. 

MORE ON ADOPTING OUR DOGS... 

> COVID-19 UPDATE:  PLEASE SUBMIT AN ONLINE ADOPTION APPLICATION AND A MEMBER OF OUR ADOPTIONS TEAM WILL REACH OUT TO YOU.  Please visit our web site at HSGKC.ORG for an adoption application, our current COVID-19 adoption protocol, and other adoption info. 

> If you decide you'd like to adopt one of the pets you meet, we reserve the pet for you but we generally don't send the pet home with you that day. We’ll instead schedule a pick up date and time that’s convenient for you.   

> Our goal is to send you home with a healthy pet and any information and support you may need to help your new pet adjust to his or her new home.  All of our dogs & puppies have been spayed or neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, treated for fleas & ticks, tested for heartworms (7 mo. and over), and are on monthly heartworm preventative. Puppies who are too young to receive all the necessary puppy boosters and/or first rabies shot may be brought back to us for those vaccines at no extra charge. You will also receive a leash, collar, coupons for pet supplies and services, toys, and educational materials. And we'll give your dog a bath before he or she goes home! 

> Please note that we prefer and may require a fenced yard for many of our dogs.  Exceptions are made on an individual basis depending on the dog's needs, the person's dog experience, the dog's and person's activity levels, home environment and other factors. 

Thank you for searching for a shelter pet!

Phone: 913.521.2339

animal.description:
**Courtesy Listing-please contact them directly**

::AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION::
MIKE (aka SPIKE) is an energetic, too smart for his own good, furry love bug!! Unfortunately his owner became ill and needed to move in with his family for assisted care. His owner was completely heart broken to not be able to take Spike with him. We took Spike into our care and reassured his dad that we will do all that we can to make sure Spike gets a good loving home. 
Spike is an approximately 4 years old neutered McNab Dog (commonly referred to as a McNab Shepherd or McNab Collie). As you can see in the pictures, Spike’s nose is “abnormal”. While with his previous owner he got amazing vet care and was diagnosed with Discoid Lupus Erythematosus (DLE or just Lupus). This is a non-contagious skin condition. 
According to VCAhospitals.com, “dogs with Discoid Lupus Erythematosus (DLE) develop crusting and scabbing of the skin, most commonly around the nose, as well as a loss of skin pigmentation in the affected area” 
It is an auto-immune disease and the underlying cause is unknown. After some trial & error treatments Spike has greatly improved simply by taking a daily dose of Prednisone (a steroid prescribed by the veterinarian) and having a prescription cream.
Spike would do fantastic in an active home and would love to have a job. He is one of the smartest dogs we have met. It may take some time for him to warm up to a new environment but once he does he is totally engaged in the family. It is important that his forever family have an understanding of how DLE can effect him such as using proper protection on his nose while in the sun for long periods of time. UV light can be harsh on a bald nose. He also has a condition called Pannus which is autoimmune and requires protection from the sun and daily eyedrops.  He is willing to wear his Doggles when he is outdoors with his people but it takes some convincing. Veterinarians and Google are a great source of information on Pannus and DLE.
Spike would love to meet you to see if he could be yours forever. Please don’t be scared of his mild “special needs”. As I always say, adopting a new family member, no matter the needs, isn’t a challenge, it’s just an adjustment. Call or text us if you would like to set up a meet & greet with this special boy!! PJ @ Fetch Cares 540-383-7522, Tori @ Fetch Cares 540-383-7521
#needsahome #fosteringsaveslives #fosterdog #fosterdogsofinstagram #fetchcares #fetchparkcity #parkcitydogs #mcnabdog 
July 19, 2020 UPDATE: 
Spike who we now refer to as Mike (he doesn’t seem to mind ?). As you may remember, Mike was diagnosed with Lupus which causes lesions and crusting of the skin usually around the nose and face. Taking care of him following a recent flare up has been challenging, but he is certainly worth it. He has been visiting the specialist dermatologist at Blue Pearl, Dr. Layne, who has been wonderful. You may also remember that Mike has an autoimmune issue called Pannus that affects his eyes. To care for his eyes, he has been seeing the specialist ophthalmologist at Blue Pearl, Dr. Disney who has been awesome. Unfortunately the symptoms for both Lupus and Pannus are exasperated by UV light and, of course, one of Mikes’s favorite things to do is sunbathe. Dr. Layne recommended a nose cover and RexSpec goggles which are specifically designed for dogs with these types of conditions. He sure looks handsome in his gear but, as you can imagine, it takes GREAT patience for him to get used to wearing them. He has been doing really well considering how weird it must feel for him to be wearing them. One of our Fetch staff members, Christie, has taken on Mike as her “project”. She takes him swimming, hiking, car rides, works on training etc. He has been living the life that every dog dreams of. He is completely in love with her and it’s so awesome all of the socialization and active exposure he has been getting. However, Mike is looking for his forever home. Mike would make a amazing dog for someone who would be willing to take him into their family knowing he has these lifelong conditions. You wouldn’t be sorry, this boy loves his people with every inch of his big heart. 
If you would like to meet Mike contact us at 435-777-3771 or fetchcares@gmail.com #fosteringsaveslives #fosterdog #fosterdogsofinstagram #fetchcares #fetchparkcity #parkcitydogs #mcnabdog

animal.description: Meet Prince! He's a goofy, loveable two-ish year old boy who is eager to play. He's a silly boy who has had a rough go of his early life. Shelter records prior to his arrival at Fur Angels indicate he may have been part of a cruelty investigation. After lots of TLC in the shelter and even more in foster, Prince is learning that people can be trusted and that life can be a lot of good, silly fun. Prince shies away from loud noises and has some anxiety that is manageable with Trazadone as needed. He is also crate trained and will take space in his crate when things get too chaotic for him. He is skittish and slow to warm up to new people, but once he does, it's game on and time to snuggle and play! Prince loves spending time in his fosters' home office and is always nearby. He loves napping with the humans and will happily cuddle up on the bed for a good snooze. He loves any toy he can chew, tear, or shred and is especially fond of squeaky toys. Treats are always welcome for this guy, and he is intelligent and loves training, though he can be easily distracted. Prince loves to play in the backyard and to go for walks and runs, and he would love a good running buddy or hiking pal as much as he would love to loaf around and be a home body. Prince enjoys the company of large dogs and/or young dogs the most but does well with energetic, friendly smaller pups as well. He does well with his foster sibling kitties who are quite familiar with large, curious dogs, but he may be too curious and playful for a kitty that's easily startled or fearful of dogs. He is working on his basic manners and will need a home where his people will help him develop into the best dog he can be (and we know he can be great!). Prince has an adoption fee of $250.00. Check him out at furangelsas.com/adopt today!

animal.description:
MEET JONI MITCHELL!!

Underdog Rescue does not physically have this dog in its possession. She is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A4498990.

Isn't Joni pretty? She's been at the shelter for more than 60 days now and she'd love to find her furever home. Joni is shy when she sees people that she doesn't know and that could be why she hasn't found her perfect home yet. She gets scared when the shelter staff tries to leash her but once she's on the leash, she loves to get out of her kennel to walk or go to the play yard. Once she gets out to the yard, she loves to do the zoomies and play. And, once she gets to know you, she will come to you for affection and pets with her tail wagging.

Joni needs an adopter that understands that it's going to take a while for her to get comfortable in a new home with people that she doesn't know. If you can give Joni the time, patience and loving home that she needs, then come and meet her today!! Please bring any dogs that you already have at home to come and meet her too.

If you are interested in saving this pet, please reach out via this link: https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/foster/BPAZ/Dog

To actually visit with this pup, please make an appointment here: https://mcaccappointments.as.me/adopt. NOTE: People who sign up for these appointments often no-show, and we have seen that you can generally show up and let them know you are there to meet this particular dog and the shelter will squeeze you in, except from 12-3PM or closer to the 6PM closing time. (Please know this is not a guarantee). If the dog is at risk, please ask for a supervisor to meet that particular dog.

*Please Note: This animal is courtesy posted for the Maricopa County Shelter; UNDERDOG RESCUE DOES NOT HAVE THIS DOG. MCACC is located at 2500 S. 27th Avenue, Phoenix. Different adoption fees/policy may apply. Please visit MCACC's website http://www.maricopa.gov/pets/locations.aspx for hours. You may also wish to call 602-506-7387 (PETS) and provide the animal's A# above to verify is still available.

She has been working on her potty training and is doing fantastic! She is working on crate training, leash training, and all the fun stuff. She is a very smart girl!! She is social with kids and other dogs. She does chase cats. 

 If interested in sweet Jersey please send in an application as the first step towards adoption www.soardogs.org 

Adoption donation required. This covers altering, DAP series vaccinations to date of adoption, Bordetella Vaccination, Rabies vaccination if over four months, Microchip, Deworming, heartworm test (if over 8 months), monthly flea/heartworm prevention to date, grooming, full veterinary examination, and temperament evaluation. Please e-mail us for more information or go to our website https://soardogs.org/adoption-application for an application. Thank you very much! 


All SOAR dogs go through a ten-day quarantine period to ensure they are healthy, before being adopted. We do not operate on a first come first serve basis, but screen applicants in order to find the best fit for our adoptable dogs.

Animal Profile: Betty, also goes by Bear arrived in Seattle on 5/17 from California. She is estimated to be 1 year old and weighs 50 lbs. She was surrendered to a high kill shelter in California with four other dogs. The owners said all four dogs were outside only dogs. Our volunteer transporter reports that Betty is shy and overwhelmed but does better once outside the kennel environment. She is interested in things and will welcome attention from people. Seattle

Foster Update: Bear actually found a home but unfortunately was returned back to us due to no fault of her own. She takes some time to warm up, but then is the sweetest girl. She will give kisses sometimes and when she's comfortable with you she is very treat motivated. She is crate trained and is most comfortable in her crate when she isn't sure what to do or nervous. She knows "go home" means go to her crate. She is perfect on a leash and doesn't pull. She knows sit, shake, "bump it" (I make a fist and she bumps it with her nose). She is fully potty trained, she has the best inside manners, and chill throughout the day. She is respectful of the inside and boundaries. She isn't allowed in the kitchen or bathroom and I've never had an issue with her testing it. She doesn't fetch yet but loves to chase the resident dog and toys in the yard. She enjoys laying out in the front yard and sunbathing. She is getting more and more comfortable out and around people but still is reserved and doesn't enjoy a lot of attention. It just takes time with her and the more positive experiences she has with people the more comfortable she'll become. She does great with the resident dog after they had a chance to get to know each other so slow introductions are a must.

Betty's ideal home will be someone who has previous dog experience, no small kids, is active, is willing to continue her training and will be patient with her. she requires a stable home.

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $500 which includes spay/neuter, all core vaccinations, microchip, heartworm test and health certificate. Your adoption fee may be tax deductible as Dog Gone Seattle is a federal 501c3 organization. Apply online: www.doggoneseattle.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
"NalaLee is a beautiful girl with a sad past. Approximately 1-1/2 years old, and because she was mistreated by being made to live
in a crate for most of her life, her hind legs did not develop properly.
When we received her the hind legs were crippled up but she was determined to walk! Now that she has been in a foster home and free to roam the house and yard, her legs are improving. She lives with other dogs and does fine but, understandably, is very leary of humans until she gets to know you - which sometimes is quite quickly, other times she keeps her distance. She would do best with a quiet home that will give her love and exercise. She is not trusting of children and we think kids were mean to her as a puppy. Very sad past but she has the ability to be a wonderful pet for someone who will take the time with her." NalaLee is housetrained and good on a leash.

Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, microchip and rabies and other core vaccinations.

animal.description:
Maggie is an absolutely AMAZING 2 year old mix breed girl that has had a super hard life and is desperately searching for a forever family able to spoil her rotten. What Maggie lacks in front teeth (due to chewing on a chain) she makes up for in smiles and cuddles for her humans; wanting nothing more than to be with her family as much as possible. Lower energy (but still very young so able to get up and go when the urge hits her), Maggie's favorite hobbies include napping in a sunny spot on the floor, napping on a soft spot on the couch, napping with her humans, barking at birds in the backyard, and eating all the snacks she can get.

Maggie is potty trained, spayed, up to date on all her vaccines, and heartworm negative. She has not been cat tested, but does well with other friendly dogs after a slow 3 to 5 day crate and rotate introduction period (as her way of "talking" when she is super happy sounds a bit like a growl and can confuse brand new dogs that don't know her).

Maggie LOVES children, but would be just as happy with ANY kind of family that is ready to make her a priority and one of their own!

animal.description:
MEET JOHNNY!!

Underdog Rescue does not physically have this dog in its possession. He is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A4497475.

Look at that big smile on Johnny's face. He's still smiling even though he's been at the shelter for more than 60 days now and he's ready to go home! All of the volunteers that have taken Johnny out for a walk say he is fun to walk. He pulls a bit when he first gets out of his kennel because he's so happy to get going but once he starts walking, he slows down and takes in his surroundings. He loves his treats and will "sit" and "shake" for them. He even knows how to "high five"!! He recently went out for the day with a foster and they said he did great. He rides well in the car and went to the park to burn off some energy. He got a hamburger treat to end his great day out. His foster says he is a fun, confident boy. And, he's potty trained!!

Johnny has reacted to other dogs in the shelter so if you have another dog at home, please bring them with you to meet him. Johnny would love to go home soon. Please come and meet him today!!

If you are interested in saving this pet, please reach out via this link: https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/foster/BPAZ/Dog

To actually visit with this pup, please make an appointment here: https://mcaccappointments.as.me/adopt. NOTE: People who sign up for these appointments often no-show, and we have seen that you can generally show up and let them know you are there to meet this particular dog and the shelter will squeeze you in, except from 12-3PM or closer to the 6PM closing time. (Please know this is not a guarantee). If the dog is at risk, please ask for a supervisor to meet that particular dog.

*Please Note: This animal is courtesy posted for the Maricopa County Shelter; UNDERDOG RESCUE DOES NOT HAVE THIS DOG. MCACC is located at 2500 S. 27th Avenue, Phoenix. Different adoption fees/policy may apply. Please visit MCACC's website http://www.maricopa.gov/pets/locations.aspx for hours. You may also wish to call 602-506-7387 (PETS) and provide the animal's A# above to verify is still available.

animal.description:
Meet Sam! estimated date of birth is may 2020, currently he is 9 pounds.

This baby boy was found in a deep ditch by a construction area; no one knows for how long Sam had been in that ditch suffering, starving, thirsty, and with no protection. We suspect he was thrown in there and probably suffered from abuse. A person heard him crying and DRWB went to his rescue. Poor Sam was in bones, very hungry and afraid.

Since his rescue he was transferred to a loving foster parent that owns a few cats, a senior golden retriever and a senior poodle. Sam has bonded with the golden retriever, even sleeps with her!

Sam is very timid, which is totally understandable given that he was the victim of abuse and the time in the ditch caused him to be afraid. Despite all of this Sam likes humans, he is not a biter and has never attempted to bite anyone; on the contrary, he is very passive and cowards when he feels he is in danger.

Sam needs a family that will give him lots of love, patience, and show him that this world can be a better place; he just needs to build confidence in himself and in humanity. He is a sweet boy that only wants to be loved, he enjoys cuddling with his foster parent, and sitting by her side to watch TV. He is not a barker.

Sam requires a calm environment, a secure place with no openings or easy escape, he will probably try to run away the first few days after moving to a new home. But he will adjust and learn to trust his new human. A home with another sweet dog would be a big plus.

We don't recommend Sam going to a home with children, as he is afraid of loud noises and abrupt moves.

He will need to learn to walk on leash and get used to traffic noises.

This boy just needs a chance to thrive. He is a true gem, he only needs love to work its magic for him to come out of his shell and leave behind all of the bad memories and experiences he suffered at a very young age.

PLEASE only serious and experienced dog owners.

animal.description:
For more pics , videos and information about Jackson, please find us on Instagram @SymbioticSuffolk or Facebook @SymbioticInc
.
Who can resist that giant underbite!!! Jackson has that face that will win you over every time and a loving, wonderful personality that steal your heart. If you are looking to add a new member to your family, please consider Jackson. We promise he will give you all the love you could ever ask for! Jackson is an amazing dog and his only real short coming is no one ever cared enough to show him some basic dog manners. He is very well balanced, loves people, likes to play with other dogs, doesn’t have any physical or behavioral issues, not overly energetic; he just needs someone who will give him a little patience and time to learn some basic rules. He has been in foster with two professional trainers for the last month and has done amazing developing his "good-boy" skills! Also, his adoption INCLUDES 6 one-hour virtual sessions with the trainers who have been fostering him so we can make sure he transitions happily into his new home and you have support to help him polish up his doggie manners.

Below are Jackson’s highlights and things to know:

-Great with other dogs (with proper intros of course)
-Very playful loving personality, but not too high energy.
-Might just be the goofiest dog ever, if you are looking for someone to make you smile, Jackson is your man!
-Not food aggressive
-Neutered, up to date with vaccines, and microchipped 
-Jackson is working on his crate manners.
-For anyone who has some dog experience and is willing to continue working with Jackson on the basics, he will be an AMAZING score of a dog. 

Symbiotic Inc has a required minimum $360 adoption donation upon the completion of the adoption (it is tax deductible!)

Jackson's adoption INCLUDES 6 one-hour virtual sessions with a professional trainer from Lucky Dogs Training. These sessions are at no additional charge and are included with his adoption!! www.LuckyDogstraining.net

If you think Jackson may be a good fit for your family, please visit our website to find out more about our application process.
https://symbioticinc.org/adoption-application 
.
Please note, if you send us an inquiry via PetFinder, our response may very likely go to your spam/junk folder. Please email us directly at info@symbioticinc.org with any questions rather than using the PetFinder ‘inquiry’ button.

Creek is a fabulous Catahoula female that has tons of energy and is super smart!  She loves to play and is extremely intuitive.  If you are active and need a buddy, she is your gal!  If you already have a dog – then she is not for you.  She needs to be the ONLY pet.  She will be a great family dog, but needs to be the only family pet.  Trust us, you will not regret only having her as she will form a bond that will be unbreakable!

If you are interested in adopting Creek, please email sln2310@yahoo.com and request an application. Once your application has been received and reviewed, you will be contacted via email or phone by one of our volunteers. After your application is approved, the foster parent for the dog you have selected will contact you to answer any questions you may have and determine if that dog is a good match for your family. 
If you have no particular dog in mind, we will be happy to keep your application on file and notify you if the right dog should come into rescue. Catahoula Rescue of New England is an all-volunteer group. Dogs in our program are fostered by volunteers. The foster homes care for our dogs as if they were their own. All dogs have received vaccinations appropriate to age and are spayed or neutered. 
Creek’s adoption donation is $400 which includes Rabies, DHLPP, Bordetella, fecal test, heartworm test when appropriate and is on preventative, microchip, and neuter. We do not have a physical shelter, all of our dogs are fostered in individual foster homes across the New England and Canada.

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Haayyy!!! I'm Rocky. They gave me this name because I'm a fighter. I have a pretty sad backstory, but none of that matters anymore. New life. New name. New me!! I was pretty lost and alone and not sure how to handle the good life, so the good people of SSOMN sent me to learn the basics (and then some!) at Premier K9 Center of Minnesota. I learned to be nice to strangers, that kitties are not for eating and that I have to tolerate other dogs. But all that aside, I'd rather have a home to myself. No dogs. No cats and No small humans. Just me and my human to play and cuddle up at night. Rocky is a stubborn 3 1/2 year old neutered male. He is up to date on vaccines and heartworm negative. He has completed intense rehabilitation training and is hanging out in his foster home until his forever family finds him. He will require significant breed experience and a strong handler to remind him he doesn't make the rules. If you think he might be your guy, you can submit an adoption application here: https://www.savingshepherdsofmn.org/info/adoption

animal.description:
Dash is a super sleek, handsome one year old high energy ACD mix who is roughly about 50 lbs.    He’s right there with our top ‘most photogenic’ dogs and photographs beautifully.    His coloration resembles a Doberman but his size, build and temperament reflect that of an ACD.   Dash is up-to-date on all medical and is an extremely handsome fellow.    We know with a little time and attention, this fellow will make the right person a loving, smart and attentive pet.     Dash was surrendered because of his high energy level and the time and attention he requires and deserves.   While he loves to play ball and frisbee, he doesn’t care to return them or bring them back to you.  

This 15 month old dog has been in two households and his energy level outlasted his owners.    He needs a family who can provide him exercise BOTH during a normal routine day AND while the owner is otherwise occupied.    He absolutely requires a fenced in yard and preferably another high energy companion pet. 

Dash walks well on the leash and, while a little timid and hesitant initially with new people; he warms up quickly allowing you to handle his mouth, ears and feet.    He’s good with the veterinarian, children and other dogs but is an unknown with cats.

Go on line to https://www.godbeycreekcaninerescue.org to complete an application for Dash.    To schedule an appointment to meet this handsome hound or for more information, contact skylara@godbeycreekcaninerescue.org, mariamw@godbeycreekcaninerescue.org OR phone 336.972.4511.

animal.description:
Rayla is in Vancouver, WA and ready for a family! We need someone with no other dogs or with a male dog, and someone who owns their home so we do not have to worry about breed issues with a rental.

Rayla is a sweet girl! She is around 2 years old. She is happiest when sleeping on the couch with her people and getting belly rubs. She has been through a lot of trauma recently, with the death of her human and going into rescue. She is adjusting well and has been mostly tail wags and smiles. She would prefer to be with someone who is home a lot or able to take her with them on their adventures. She loves all people she meets but has not been around kids. She has never shown any aggression to people and loves everyone that meets her. She is learning her doggy social skills. She likes to play with goofy boys. She could get along with a goofy or chill male dog with proper SLOW introductions. She would be totally fine being the one and only center of attention too. It was said that she spent her nights, sharing a pillow with her human. Rayla has not been cat tested. She is learning her basic obedience and leash skills. Crate trained and house broken. Rayla is going to be an amazing companion for someone who wants company. She is so loving and her presence is delightful! 

Rayla is fully vetted. We are working on loosing a couple of of pounds now. 

Please inquire by submitting an application to jaime@threelittlepittiesrescue.org

Application link: https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/21733/generic

Please go to our website to see more about our rescue and what we do! We are very proud of our hard work in saving as many animals as we can, giving them what they need, and matching them with the right families.

animal.description:
Ski is a sweet girl who loves attention and belly rubs. She adores squeaky toys but has a mission to quickly remove the stuffing. Ski recently had some stitches removed and is loving that she is now allowed to run and chase her toys. She loves to play for a while or go for a walk and then take a long nap on her dog bed or the couch.

Ski is new to living as part of a family. She is gradually gaining confidence and learning that she does not need to be afraid of new sounds or experiences. When she is frightened, she usually hides behind people that she trusts, or barks. She needs someone with the time and patience to train her.

Ski is making great progress with house training. She does her business whenever we take her out, but so far, she does not ask to go out. In foster care, we have been taking her out every 3 hours or so and she has been doing great on this schedule.

Fill out an adoption application to schedule your own private meet and greet with this furry friend.

Follow us on Facebook for additional updates and sneak peeks of new dogs! https://www.facebook.com/reachrescue

animal.description:
Tad had a lot of worry and sadness to him when he was rescued from a kill shelter in Texas. After a few days we realized something may be causing him discomfort in his hips. After xrays we found out he had a shattered pelvis. The doctor couldn't believe he was even walking. Even through all of that pain he just wanted comfort and love. After seeing a specialist it was determined his breaks were too healed to do anything about, except pain management and rehabilitation. 
Tad will be starting rehab soon. He may need it for 4-6 months. He is 1-2 years old. He's good with other dogs and cats. Older children in the home would be best. He's learning to be kenneled and to go potty on pads between potty breaks. Now that he isn't in pain he tries to play with the other dogs in the home. He loves to snuggle in bed. When you stop petting him he'll growl toward you for your attention or gently grab your hand with his mouth to keep petting him. He gets excited to greet you when you come home and will cry and bark and paw at the back of your legs to let you know how happy he is you have returned. He loves car rides and walks. He has also gained some weight and doesn't look so emaciated.

animal.description:
The boy, waiting to roll full steam ahead!

Hi there! My name is Locomotive, Loco for short. I am a 1-year-old, neutered male, Shepherd Mix weighing around 25 lbs. I am here because The Animal Pad rescued me from a shelter in Ensenada called Ellos Son La Razon. Currently, I am working on potty training and leash training, I just have a few accidents here and there that my foster is helping me out with. I dont have leash training yet, but I am also working on it! Maybe you can lend a paw?

I am very shy and timid and with help from my foster mama and my doggie sibling, I have bloomed! I have even started to cuddle on the bed and it makes her so happy! My foster believes its because I had an abusive past getting bullied. Even though I require a lot of time and patience for me to trust you...I just want love all day every day. Ill even whine when you stop petting me. My favorite activity is getting lots of belly rubs. But Im also a huge sucker for treats!! I am doggo and little hooman friendly. If you're willing to put in the time, then I am willing to put in my trust in you. Pinky Pawmise.

My perfect furever home would be a place where I have hoomans/big or small and definitely other doggos to bring out the dog I am. I adore being with other dogs! I have struggled with my past life but I would like to move on with a lot of patience and love. I will need some decompression time, but I do love fully once I trust. My adoption fee is $400 and that includes spaying/neutering, shots, and microchip. If you want to take me home, please fill out the form on the website here https://theanimalpad.org/adoption-application/
